---
import SectionHeading from "./SectionHeading.astro";

const points = [
  {
    title: "Open source",
    body: "AGPL-3.0. Every reviewer, every verdict, the whole gate. Nothing about how your code is judged is hidden behind a service.",
  },
  {
    title: "Self-hostable",
    body: "Runs anywhere code can run, local or any CI. It drives the agent backends you already use (Claude Code, Codex, Pi) and reuses your own auth and billing.",
  },
  {
    title: "No lock-in",
    body: "Your policy is one declarative file in your repo. Take it with you. There's no proprietary format and no black box to migrate off of.",
  },
];
---

<section class="section trust" id="open">
  <div class="container">
    <SectionHeading title="Open source and self-hostable.">
      Read every reviewer, run them on your own infrastructure through the model
      provider and billing you already use, and own the gate outright. The
      reviewers, the verdicts, and the aggregation are all in the open.
    </SectionHeading>

    <div class="trust-grid">
      {
        points.map((p, i) => (
          <article class="trust-card" data-reveal style={`--reveal-delay:${i * 70}ms`}>
            <h3>{p.title}</h3>
            <p>{p.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <div class="honest" data-reveal>
      <div class="honest-mark" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <path d="M12 3 4 6v6c0 4.5 3.2 7.3 8 9 4.8-1.7 8-4.5 8-9V6l-8-3Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
          <path d="M9.2 12.2l1.9 1.9 3.9-4.2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="honest-body">
        <h3>Early software, fails closed.</h3>
        <p>
          Bastion is early and moving fast. The runner, the gate, and the Claude
          Code, Codex, and Pi backends run reviewers for real. Anything not yet
          implemented <strong>returns block instead of pass</strong>, so an
          unfinished capability can't wave code through by claiming a review it
          never ran.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .trust-grid {
    margin-top: clamp(2rem, 1rem + 3vw, 3rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .trust-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }
  .trust-card {
    padding: clamp(1.1rem, 0.8rem + 1vw, 1.5rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    background: var(--paper-raised);
  }
  .trust-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .trust-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }

  .honest {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 0.9rem + 1.4vw, 1.8rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--pass-line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    background: linear-gradient(
      to bottom right,
      var(--pass-bg),
      var(--paper-raised) 55%
    );
  }
  .honest-mark {
    flex: none;
    color: var(--pass-ink);
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }
  .honest-body h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .honest-body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
</style>
